---
import GetStartedLayout from "../../layouts/GetStartedLayout.astro";
---

<GetStartedLayout
  title="Mission"
  current="mission"
  description="Why Prism exists and what the design system is here to accomplish."
>
  <header class="page-head">
    <h1 data-i18n="getStarted.mission.h2">Mission</h1>
    <p class="intro" data-i18n="getStarted.lede">
      Align on why Prism exists, how we judge good work, and the vocabulary we share before you open
      foundations or components.
    </p>
  </header>

  <section class="block">
    <p class="prose" data-i18n="getStarted.mission.p1">
      Prism connects design intent and shipped UI: a single place for tokens, reusable components, and
      written guidance so teams do not reinvent basics in every feature.
    </p>
    <p class="prose" data-i18n="getStarted.mission.p2">
      We exist to make high-quality interfaces the default—faster handoffs, fewer one-off styles, and
      experiences that stay legible, inclusive, and calm as the product grows.
    </p>
  </section>

  <p class="next">
    <a class="next-link" href="/get-started/principles" data-i18n="getStarted.nextPrinciples">Design principles</a>
  </p>
</GetStartedLayout>
